 handle unsupported features. The task specifies that tests should run in a Native environment by default, but unsupported class loading might throw an error. I wonder if I could avoid this issue by generating a class at compile time. Creating a test for just the `getMethods` might be okay, but the task demands more coverage. I’ll also need the library JAR path for the child URLClassLoader.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Exploring class loading in Scala**\\\\n\\\\nI'm trying to figure out whether to load the Scala library from the parent or child class. If the child can't load Scala, that poses a problem. Ideally, I want the child to take precedence for Akka classes, while using the parent for current Scala and JavaX classes. If the parent has Akka classes as well, the default parent-first method will load `Http2` from there, which won't use any custom ALPN settings. This needs careful consideration!\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_8D26aAxzzTKcbrLbUqCWIPyy|fc_06ca1d19fe6b72bd0169fb130a956c8196bd41c242dbd59af6\", \"name\": \"bash\", \"arguments\": {\"command\": \"rg \\\"isUnsupportedFeatureError|NativeImageSupport\\\" tests/src -n | head -50\"}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 1220, \"output\": 1730, \"cacheRead\": 31232, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 34182, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1778062066170, \"responseId\": \"resp_06ca1d19fe6b72bd0169fb12f2c6848196a29984a94cc98643\"}}\n2161:[recv] {\"type\": \"turn_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Considering test setup for dynamic class loading**\\n\\nOkay, so I’m thinking about the dynamic-class-loading pattern and how it can handle unsupported features. The task specifies that tests should run in a Native environment by default, but unsupported class loading might throw an error. I wonder if I could avoid this issue by generating a class at compile time. Creating a test for just the `getMethods` might be okay, but the task demands more coverage. I’ll also need the library JAR path for the child URLClassLoader.\\n\\n**Exploring class loading in Scala**\\n\\nI'm trying to figure out whether to load the Scala library from the parent or child class. If the child can't load Scala, that poses a problem. Ideally, I want the child to take precedence for Akka classes, while using the parent for current Scala and JavaX classes. If the parent has Akka classes as well, the default parent-first method will load `Http2` from there, which won't use any custom ALPN settings. This needs careful consideration!\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_06ca1d19fe6b72bd0169fb12f37a248196b3907553b3735541\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABp-xMK17w_c3gNumtNBpGIH0wK1iPS6uPZOt4NgMUmdJlv7xLa-IJw1Z8oJfGEIiA-r6mXNkXG6BQou3roTeP7f5zUGCB3nAYdqR2dInIoFy3egCljiwbVm5f1nXlyQoVlFaHA6Ug5ZbRONSprG2c1wCEEakS-YF_eaT6QvFeTkbq0v7Mv3nMtgV1u8TTnciMQ2owt2VcyPfqBgMebGY0Ru5gb9WQdcnzzW9VCAAtmQ6AfmjuHGxtny8WISzL8V_EVMQ4DKakq1xMDud7IpwuIUqXhxHYsJaDxhdmbe4q9C__iyWsVar14YB_ZiRUqOUjXsbsnHK52sejbyt_CFoD-z2vfrMKbhqvccpIgpsL7tqECgYg-MKSBecd6ggyY-W6Xvre9gLORAThhqlR_cwcNxdrfc-l6flDSIkf5QsWqJIf4yuvb7tHaWSz-a-E1UM3Yp4gS1uC8xDCprOq1pP-JPYcILmKSBRs9HPSGqZMnfbmzFQiOTcWSDOsb1DutOxqIUHqmha1ZtmhlHUkDbFwMNukAshctLZzrrW9FGhNxYsK3l0KEsJ7H2eWLPxH_xFilz_oGHj0pq4yrouz0cOZ7WTXDH26ziBo65qiegaIEusqpnZN4eP5GLCOs8heP5rNSfEkBuBsT8wQT4D923FlIOldJMV9bqTJVUc8k72QIrLwCAxyr97KEzvVkRw4yuFzjTibiLkCLEWFaeJle7kPrNgd8wMnZCAxZqIZSxBri9r5W5Ia3kNI3gD4HMZl8c_6EkvhwQwaDF4raW5--D98LA2S1tCvnNsQpZztnPflxdDjS2rAidezoLQZiI3HhOYVAxHr7x024WBsGnWAwyxCc2eyXLt0-Jy7VAH-vMKyXjBKDsr__C2hXkwCZKyAC6vdxhOq293iOxvEwWEWtCVBvdreKpDl0LxKUNeTOyZweECVo0l0lH2tMPmZO2h2g_Vb-mlwXaKqItxT8BkrMu5hDhk-TGJhj1A_4P3UlLBg_lQwQmd-P8FXETJaoQig_VWuoKsut-0BgY8aHjXwKNKi95