king about the dynamic-class-loading pattern and how it can handle unsupported features. The task specifies that tests should run in a Native environment by default, but unsupported class loading might throw an error. I wonder if I could avoid this issue by generating a class at compile time. Creating a test for just the `getMethods` might be okay, but the task demands more coverage. I’ll also need the library JAR path for the child URLClassLoader.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Exploring class loading in Scala**\\\\n\\\\nI'm trying to figure out whether to load the Scala library from the parent or child class. If the child can't load Scala, that poses a problem. Ideally, I want the child to take precedence for Akka classes, while using the parent for current Scala and JavaX classes. If the parent has Akka classes as well, the default parent-first method will load `Http2` from there, which won't use any custom ALPN settings. This needs careful consideration!\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_8D26aAxzzTKcbrLbUqCWIPyy|fc_06ca1d19fe6b72bd0169fb130a956c8196bd41c242dbd59af6\", \"name\": \"bash\", \"arguments\": {\"command\": \"rg \\\"isUnsupportedFeatureError|NativeImageSupport\\\" tests/src -n | head -50\"}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 1220, \"output\": 1730, \"cacheRead\": 31232, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 34182, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1778062066170, \"responseId\": \"resp_06ca1d19fe6b72bd0169fb12f2c6848196a29984a94cc98643\"}, \"toolResults\": [{\"role\": \"toolResult\", \"toolCallId\": \"call_8D26aAxzzTKcbrLbUqCWIPyy|fc_06ca1d19fe6b72bd0169fb130a956c8196bd41c242dbd59af6\", \"toolName\": \"bash\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"tests/src/org.wildfly.openssl/wildfly-openssl-java/2.1.1.Final/src/test/java/org_wildfly