ld try something like `Flow[ByteString].alsoTo(Sink.foreach(_ =>())).prepend(Source.maybe)` for the flow shape from ByteString to ByteString. There’s definitely something there!\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Clarifying Scala imports**\\\\n\\\\nI’m thinking about the Scala compiler and its references, but wait, what about the runtime? The test class currently only has imports for compilation. I wonder if the child runner object is in the same class file? Actually, it seems that top-level imports apply to all blocks within the package. That’s an important detail to remember when structuring the code. Just need to keep that in mind!\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Evaluating class loading issues**\\\\n\\\\nI see that the SupportChildRunner class is loaded child-first, which is good, but its constant pool references Http through the child loader. There's a current failure happening, suggesting there's no invocation. I think I need to make some edits to the transport. It looks like I need to import Keep as well. I'll look into the details of this error and make the necessary adjustments to ensure everything functions smoothly.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_SwYNuAejJUlG6Z83aZquadpX|fc_06ca1d19fe6b72bd0169fb144dffa88196bf46d90079136ddf\", \"name\": \"edit\", \"arguments\": {\"path\": \"tests/src/com.typesafe.akka/akka-http-core_2.13/10.5.3/src/test/scala/com_typesafe_akka/akka_http_core_2_13/Http2AlpnSupportTest.scala\", \"edits\": [{\"oldText\": \"import akka.stream.scaladsl.Flow\\nimport akka.stream.scaladsl.Sink\\nimport akka.stream.scaladsl.Source\\n\", \"newText\": \"import akka.stream.scaladsl.Flow\\nimport akka.stream.scaladsl.Keep\\nimport akka.stream.scaladsl.Sink\\nimport akka.stream.scaladsl.Source\\n\"}, {\"oldText\": \"      Flow[ByteString].mapMaterializedValue(_ => Future.successful(OutgoingConnection(localAddress, remoteAddress)))\\n\", \"newText\": \"      Flow.fromSinkAndSourceMa